  "title": "New territories: theatre, drama, and performance in post-apartheid South Africa",
  "abstract": "Greg Homann and Marc Maufort are well placed to edit this new critical analysis of South African theatre: Homann is a successful South African playwright who won the 2014 Standard Bank Young Artist Award for Theatre, and has taught in the Wits School of Arts and the South African School for Motion Picture Medium and Live Performance in Johannesburg. Maufort is Professor of English, American and Postcolonial Literatures at the University of Bruxelles, and so a logical editor for this 34th volume of Peter Lang's Dramaturgies series.",
